WEBVTT

00:00:21.813 --> 00:00:23.023
N-No…

00:00:23.773 --> 00:00:24.774
That's impossible…

00:00:25.150 --> 00:00:27.610
I can't believe the Tres Bestia
were defeated…

00:00:28.361 --> 00:00:31.322
A Soul Reaper with an Arrancar
on his back?

00:00:31.740 --> 00:00:32.949
How unusual.

00:00:33.575 --> 00:00:34.576
That being said…

00:00:34.993 --> 00:00:37.162
I know all about you,

00:00:37.996 --> 00:00:39.956
Ichigo Kurosaki.

00:00:40.832 --> 00:00:45.754
The Daten that His Majesty gave us
included information about you.

00:00:46.171 --> 00:00:48.298
You were listed
as a "Special Threat"

00:00:48.339 --> 00:00:50.341
that we should prioritize
dealing with!

00:00:52.052 --> 00:00:53.219
"Special Threat"?

00:00:55.263 --> 00:00:56.222
<i>That technique…</i>

00:00:57.390 --> 00:00:58.349
<i>the Hirenkyaku.</i>

00:01:07.734 --> 00:01:08.818
Are you guys really Qui--?

00:01:08.943 --> 00:01:09.903
Oh, my!

00:01:09.986 --> 00:01:14.949
Don't tell me that you engaged us
<i>without</i> knowing who we were?

00:01:15.658 --> 00:01:16.659
Very well!

00:01:16.868 --> 00:01:18.828
In that case…
I shall answer your question.

00:01:27.003 --> 00:01:29.756
Yes, we <i>are</i> who you think we are.

00:01:30.381 --> 00:01:31.841
We are <i>Quincies</i>.

00:01:34.719 --> 00:01:38.765
{\an8}SQUAD ONE BARRACKS -
CAPTAIN'S MEETING ROOM

00:01:37.222 --> 00:01:38.473
Quincies…

00:01:39.224 --> 00:01:40.642
Well, I figured
that would be the case,

00:01:40.767 --> 00:01:42.560
but this is quite the problem.

00:01:42.644 --> 00:01:45.021
Where is their base of operations?

00:01:46.356 --> 00:01:48.983
Unfortunately,
I have yet to find it…

00:01:49.234 --> 00:01:50.443
I see…

00:01:50.902 --> 00:01:53.780
That means we have no way
of attacking them.

00:01:55.323 --> 00:01:59.911
I'm ordering all Squad Captains
to prepare for war.

00:02:00.245 --> 00:02:02.038
The advance guard of the rebel army

00:02:02.163 --> 00:02:04.415
announced that the battle
would begin in five days,

00:02:04.749 --> 00:02:07.127
but there is no reason to believe
the words of treacherous fellows

00:02:07.252 --> 00:02:09.379
that would launch
a surprise attack.

00:02:09.796 --> 00:02:12.799
We must prepare for battle at once,
as fast as we possibly can!

00:02:13.424 --> 00:02:16.845
We must not let them
get the upper hand again!

00:02:37.407 --> 00:02:42.245
{\an8}<i>The blue skies above are hopelessly clear</i>

00:02:42.370 --> 00:02:47.417
{\an8}<i>At my wit's end, I feel a growing frustration</i>

00:02:47.834 --> 00:02:52.297
{\an8}<i>As if to laugh at us hopeless cowards</i>

00:02:52.630 --> 00:02:55.758
{\an8}<i>Countless eyes stare at us</i>

00:02:56.509 --> 00:03:02.348
{\an8}<i>This soul of mine breaks again and again</i>

00:03:02.640 --> 00:03:05.560
{\an8}<i>All I can do is hold it tight</i>

00:03:06.769 --> 00:03:11.858
{\an8}<i>Until the day it turns to ash</i>

00:03:11.858 --> 00:03:14.694
{\an8}<i>I've absorbed all of this sorrow</i>

00:03:14.819 --> 00:03:19.324
{\an8}<i>It has shaped me, painted me</i>

00:03:19.407 --> 00:03:21.910
{\an8}<i>But that's how we got here, right?</i>

00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:26.831
{\an8}<i>One step at a time, just like breathing</i>

00:03:26.998 --> 00:03:29.667
{\an8}<i>These countless scars on my palm</i>

00:03:29.792 --> 00:03:31.669
{\an8}<i>That no longer fade</i>

00:03:31.753 --> 00:03:35.423
{\an8}<i>Are my badge, my story</i>

00:03:35.673 --> 00:03:39.344
{\an8}<i>I faced the fear and shred it to pieces</i>

00:03:39.510 --> 00:03:42.513
{\an8}<i>And let it walk beside me once more</i>

00:03:42.597 --> 00:03:47.227
{\an8}BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR

00:04:09.958 --> 00:04:11.626
All shots hit their mark.

00:04:12.293 --> 00:04:13.503
What's the matter?!

00:04:13.628 --> 00:04:15.588
You can do better than this!

00:04:20.677 --> 00:04:21.636
That's weird…

00:04:23.429 --> 00:04:26.391
I heard that Quincies
only use bows.

00:04:27.433 --> 00:04:28.351
What?

00:04:35.233 --> 00:04:36.359
Kurosaki!

00:04:37.277 --> 00:04:38.278
Inoue!

00:04:38.653 --> 00:04:39.779
Look after Nel!

00:04:46.911 --> 00:04:48.162
Impressive…

00:04:48.830 --> 00:04:52.667
It makes me dismayed
by my lack of skill…

00:04:53.293 --> 00:04:54.419
Don't worry.

00:04:54.711 --> 00:04:57.130
Your arrows were a lot stronger
than Ishida's.

00:04:57.797 --> 00:05:00.008
Though it's been quite some time
since I got hit with one of them.

00:05:00.508 --> 00:05:01.467
"Ishida"?

00:05:02.260 --> 00:05:05.763
By "Ishida,"
are you referring to "Uryu Ishida"?

00:05:06.931 --> 00:05:09.600
You guys know about Ishida?

00:05:10.393 --> 00:05:14.355
Uryu Ishida's Heilig Pfeil
is weaker than mine?

00:05:15.523 --> 00:05:16.941
How odd…

00:05:17.483 --> 00:05:19.319
That's not possible.

00:05:20.028 --> 00:05:21.279
What do you mean?

00:05:21.738 --> 00:05:22.739
Whoops.

00:05:23.114 --> 00:05:25.616
Speech is silver,
silence is golden.

00:05:26.117 --> 00:05:27.910
I've said a little too much.

00:05:28.703 --> 00:05:29.579
Forgive me…

00:05:32.999 --> 00:05:35.752
Now then, it's time for me
to stop fooling around.

00:05:36.210 --> 00:05:38.921
I just received orders
from His Majesty.

00:05:39.422 --> 00:05:40.673
Just who is this "Majesty"?

00:05:41.215 --> 00:05:43.801
I have no need
to answer that question.

00:05:44.635 --> 00:05:47.680
In short, it means
you are going to die here.

00:05:48.598 --> 00:05:50.183
Now take a good look.

00:05:50.558 --> 00:05:54.771
I'm sure you've heard
about this power…

00:05:55.605 --> 00:05:58.816
A Quincy's final state, Letz Stile!

00:06:04.405 --> 00:06:07.450
<i>The Quincy secret move</i>
<i>that Ishida used before!</i>

00:06:17.752 --> 00:06:20.254
Allow me to explain…

00:06:20.588 --> 00:06:22.673
The proper name for this form is…

00:06:23.549 --> 00:06:26.302
Quincy Voll Stern Dich.

00:06:29.597 --> 00:06:31.641
We've received an update
from Jagd Armee 1.

00:06:31.849 --> 00:06:34.977
Quilge Opie is currently
engaged in battle

00:06:35.061 --> 00:06:36.687
with "Special Threat"
Ichigo Kurosaki.

00:06:37.730 --> 00:06:39.899
Then let's go…

00:06:39.982 --> 00:06:42.068
Where to, Your Majesty?

00:06:42.985 --> 00:06:44.821
Isn't it obvious?

00:06:45.446 --> 00:06:47.782
<i>An imperial order from His Majesty</i>
<i>to the Stern Ritter.</i>

00:06:48.241 --> 00:06:51.285
<i>All Stern Ritter are to</i>
<i>immediately get equipped</i>

00:06:51.411 --> 00:06:53.079
<i>and assemble at</i>
<i>the Gate of the Sun.</i>

00:06:53.579 --> 00:06:54.580
<i>Repeat…</i>

00:06:54.789 --> 00:06:55.665
<i>All Stern Ritter are to…</i>

00:06:56.165 --> 00:06:58.584
The Wandenreich is going to…

00:06:59.252 --> 00:07:02.296
invade the Soul Society.

00:07:23.484 --> 00:07:24.777
Do you feel it?

00:07:25.278 --> 00:07:27.947
The pulsation of my power…

00:07:30.116 --> 00:07:33.119
The power of the one
who shall punish you!

00:07:37.540 --> 00:07:40.918
<i>Is that the same technique</i>
<i>that Urahara told me about?</i>

00:07:46.757 --> 00:07:48.718
You seem confused.

00:07:49.051 --> 00:07:50.803
I know what you're thinking,

00:07:50.887 --> 00:07:53.139
so I shall give you
a definitive answer.

00:07:53.639 --> 00:07:55.099
It's something entirely different.

00:07:57.143 --> 00:08:01.647
The Quincy Letz Stile that you know
is a relic of the past

00:08:01.772 --> 00:08:06.694
that died out 200 years ago
due to its fragile nature.

00:08:06.819 --> 00:08:10.656
The only one who was attached to it
was Soken Ishida,

00:08:10.698 --> 00:08:13.534
who rejected our research
and evolution!

00:08:13.701 --> 00:08:16.704
By comparison,
this Quincy Voll Stern Dich…

00:08:18.539 --> 00:08:21.459
the difference in power is
as far apart as heaven and earth!

00:08:22.752 --> 00:08:23.753
I see…

00:08:23.836 --> 00:08:26.547
I don't know about your history,

00:08:26.631 --> 00:08:29.967
but in short,
it's different from Ishida's power.

00:08:30.968 --> 00:08:32.261
I'm glad to hear that.

00:08:32.553 --> 00:08:35.556
If Ishida transformed into
something as creepy as that…

00:08:35.598 --> 00:08:37.850
I might cut him down by mistake.

00:08:38.809 --> 00:08:40.770
You're easing up on your blade.

00:08:42.563 --> 00:08:45.858
Getsugatensho!

00:08:50.279 --> 00:08:52.114
That's not good.

00:08:55.034 --> 00:08:57.620
You should aim your strikes.

00:08:57.954 --> 00:08:58.955
Damn it!

00:09:00.081 --> 00:09:04.210
That said, even if you did that,
you wouldn't find any weaknesses!

00:09:05.545 --> 00:09:09.966
You called this form of mine
creepy, didn't you?

00:09:10.550 --> 00:09:12.051
That is the correct response.

00:09:12.677 --> 00:09:16.305
To the eyes of you
atrocious Soul Reapers,

00:09:16.389 --> 00:09:19.559
the form of we holy executioners…

00:09:19.809 --> 00:09:23.020
should be creepy and horrifying
to behold!

00:09:30.820 --> 00:09:33.614
No way!
Sotenkishun is being peeled away!

00:09:35.658 --> 00:09:38.327
Now have a taste…

00:09:39.078 --> 00:09:43.249
of my Voll Stern Dich,
the power of Piskiel!

00:09:47.003 --> 00:09:48.004
What…?!

00:09:54.844 --> 00:09:57.847
What is that monster?

00:09:59.599 --> 00:10:00.850
You assumed
we couldn't fight anymore,

00:10:00.933 --> 00:10:02.018
so you let down your guard,
didn't you?

00:10:02.476 --> 00:10:04.770
I thought we told you that
you shouldn't underestimate us…

00:10:05.438 --> 00:10:10.067
Show this cocky four-eyed monkey
your power!

00:10:10.568 --> 00:10:11.569
Ayon!

00:10:17.491 --> 00:10:18.492
What the hell…

00:10:18.993 --> 00:10:19.994
is that thing?!

00:10:20.870 --> 00:10:24.957
Ayon is a monster created through
the fusion of our left arms!

00:10:25.374 --> 00:10:27.627
He's got power,
but he's unpredictable!

00:10:31.005 --> 00:10:35.301
A monster like you could never
beat my Voll Stern Dich--!

00:10:38.971 --> 00:10:40.640
{\an8}ISHIDA RESIDENCE - ARCHIVES

00:10:41.557 --> 00:10:43.351
There's nothing of importance here…

00:10:43.643 --> 00:10:44.560
What are you doing?

00:10:46.979 --> 00:10:47.980
Ryuken!

00:10:48.648 --> 00:10:50.608
I thought I told you
not to come in here

00:10:50.608 --> 00:10:51.692
without my permission.

00:10:52.568 --> 00:10:56.530
The Soul Society and Hueco Mundo
are being invaded by someone.

00:10:57.657 --> 00:11:00.576
And they are most likely…Quincies.

00:11:01.702 --> 00:11:04.246
There shouldn't be any Quincies
in existence aside from us.

00:11:04.747 --> 00:11:06.165
Do you know something about this?!

00:11:08.084 --> 00:11:10.086
This has nothing to do with you.

00:11:11.837 --> 00:11:14.715
- Get out.
- Are you going to avoid me again?!

00:11:16.759 --> 00:11:18.469
I am the last Quincy.

00:11:19.303 --> 00:11:22.223
I have a right to know
what's going on.

00:11:26.310 --> 00:11:28.521
The answer you seek…

00:11:28.896 --> 00:11:29.855
cannot be found here.

00:11:32.733 --> 00:11:37.738
{\an8}SHORYU GATE ENTRANCE

00:11:38.989 --> 00:11:42.702
Shino, I know this probably isn't
the best time to ask this, but…

00:11:42.827 --> 00:11:43.744
What is it?

00:11:44.036 --> 00:11:45.955
Do you happen to know why
Soul Reapers and Quincies

00:11:46.038 --> 00:11:47.915
are at odds with each other
in the first place?

00:11:48.582 --> 00:11:51.877
We both share the same goal
of defeating Hollows, don't we?

00:11:51.961 --> 00:11:54.004
What?!
That's because…

00:11:56.090 --> 00:11:57.967
Wait…
Why is that?

00:11:58.884 --> 00:11:59.969
You know that in ancient times,

00:12:00.052 --> 00:12:02.888
Soul Reapers were referred to
as Balancers, don't you?

00:12:03.431 --> 00:12:04.056
S…

00:12:04.056 --> 00:12:06.559
{\an8}SQUAD 13 SIXTH SEAT -
HIDETOMO KAJOMARU

00:12:04.557 --> 00:12:05.766
Sixth Seat Kajomaru!

00:12:06.726 --> 00:12:07.810
It's an honor to see you here!

00:12:08.018 --> 00:12:10.229
Well, the alarms
haven't sounded yet,

00:12:10.646 --> 00:12:12.398
so why don't we discuss this a bit?

00:12:15.109 --> 00:12:16.610
For starters,

00:12:17.403 --> 00:12:19.822
you understand the law of
this world where souls circulate

00:12:19.905 --> 00:12:22.491
between the World of the Living
and the Soul Society, don't you?

00:12:22.742 --> 00:12:24.076
- Yes.
- Of course!

00:12:24.618 --> 00:12:25.619
Good.

00:12:26.162 --> 00:12:28.748
However, souls that become Hollows
in the World of the Living

00:12:29.248 --> 00:12:31.542
cannot return to the Soul Society.

00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:36.839
By purifying Hollows and delivering
their souls to the Soul Society,

00:12:37.214 --> 00:12:39.633
they are led back to
the normal circulation of souls.

00:12:40.259 --> 00:12:42.011
This is the job of Soul Reapers

00:12:42.094 --> 00:12:43.763
and the reason why
we are called Balancers.

00:12:44.680 --> 00:12:48.225
However, Quincies destroy
and completely extinguish

00:12:48.267 --> 00:12:49.769
souls that have become Hollows.

00:12:50.644 --> 00:12:51.896
What happens when they do that?

00:12:52.938 --> 00:12:56.275
The souls are unable to return
to the Soul Society?

00:12:56.776 --> 00:12:57.777
That's right.

00:12:58.110 --> 00:12:59.111
Normally,

00:12:59.153 --> 00:13:01.947
a balance must be maintained
between the number of souls

00:13:02.031 --> 00:13:04.617
that exist in the Soul Society
and the World of the Living.

00:13:05.367 --> 00:13:08.078
As Quincies extinguish more Hollows
in the World of the Living,

00:13:08.162 --> 00:13:11.540
the number of souls is diminished,
disrupting that natural balance…

00:13:12.333 --> 00:13:13.542
If we allow this to happen,

00:13:13.626 --> 00:13:15.711
the balance of souls
will eventually be ruined,

00:13:16.337 --> 00:13:18.756
causing the Soul Society to flow
into the World of the Living…

00:13:20.716 --> 00:13:22.885
ending in the simultaneous
destruction of both worlds.

00:13:27.807 --> 00:13:31.602
There isn't much written
about Quincies to begin with…

00:13:34.647 --> 00:13:35.648
Master…

00:13:41.695 --> 00:13:42.947
"Cannot be found <i>here</i>…"

00:13:44.156 --> 00:13:47.368
{\an8}ISHIDA RESIDENCE -
RYUKEN ISHIDA'S ROOM

00:14:05.261 --> 00:14:06.637
This is Master's--!

00:14:09.223 --> 00:14:10.683
To prevent this destruction,

00:14:11.016 --> 00:14:14.186
the Soul Society had repeatedly
approached the Quincies

00:14:14.270 --> 00:14:15.396
for a dialogue,

00:14:15.771 --> 00:14:17.690
but they were turned away
each time.

00:14:18.691 --> 00:14:21.235
The world was steadily
heading toward destruction.

00:14:21.902 --> 00:14:25.865
And after endless debate
within the Soul Society…

00:14:26.532 --> 00:14:28.576
the Quincy Extermination Operation

00:14:28.576 --> 00:14:31.036
was finally carried out
200 years ago.

00:14:32.037 --> 00:14:33.747
Our goals do not mesh

00:14:33.831 --> 00:14:36.959
and the grudge borne of
their genocide will never perish.

00:14:38.085 --> 00:14:42.047
The Soul Reapers and Quincies
have no other choice but to fight…

00:14:44.049 --> 00:14:46.427
Do you understand,
Squad Member Ryunosuke Yuki?

00:14:47.928 --> 00:14:50.264
May I…ask one question?

00:14:51.765 --> 00:14:55.853
Are we Soul Reapers
fighting this battle for justice?

00:14:58.731 --> 00:15:00.858
If there is justice
on one side or the other,

00:15:01.525 --> 00:15:03.736
it would be called self-defense
or conquest.

00:15:04.945 --> 00:15:06.280
However, this is a war.

00:15:07.323 --> 00:15:08.490
Wars take place…

00:15:09.283 --> 00:15:11.285
because both sides are just.

00:15:13.621 --> 00:15:16.707
You know why I've called you here,
don't you,

00:15:16.957 --> 00:15:21.962
{\an8}SQUAD 1 BARRACKS -
HEAD CAPTAIN'S OFFICE

00:15:17.291 --> 00:15:19.668
Squad 12 Captain Kurotsuchi?

00:15:20.210 --> 00:15:22.463
Is this about mobilizing
members of Squad 12

00:15:22.504 --> 00:15:26.050
to expunge 28,000 citizens
of the Rukon District

00:15:26.133 --> 00:15:29.470
without permission in order to
correct the balance of souls?

00:15:29.929 --> 00:15:32.181
Why didn't you get permission?

00:15:32.765 --> 00:15:36.060
Those mass disappearances
in the Rukon District

00:15:36.143 --> 00:15:40.105
reported by Squad 11's
Third Seat Ikkaku Madarame

00:15:40.189 --> 00:15:42.608
and Fifth Seat Yumichika Ayasegawa…

00:15:43.317 --> 00:15:46.236
You would have gotten permission
if things became dire.

00:15:46.779 --> 00:15:48.989
The mass extermination of Hollows
in the World of the Living

00:15:49.156 --> 00:15:52.159
by the rebel army was intentionally
done to disrupt the balance

00:15:52.284 --> 00:15:55.162
between the World of the Living
and the Soul Society.

00:15:55.663 --> 00:15:58.207
If you consider the fact that
the lives of the people

00:15:58.290 --> 00:16:00.584
of the Rukon District stopped
the collapse of both worlds,

00:16:00.668 --> 00:16:02.670
it is not that big of a loss.

00:16:03.045 --> 00:16:04.046
If I had waited for permission

00:16:04.129 --> 00:16:06.382
and the situation had escalated
beyond control,

00:16:06.465 --> 00:16:09.468
that is not something
I could take responsibility for.

00:16:09.885 --> 00:16:13.305
But if your Department of
Research and Development

00:16:13.472 --> 00:16:15.808
had reported the matter
and promptly dealt with it,

00:16:15.933 --> 00:16:19.061
we might have prevented
the current situation.

00:16:19.269 --> 00:16:20.646
You're wrong about that.

00:16:21.355 --> 00:16:24.149
The moment that the Quincy
known as Uryu Ishida

00:16:24.274 --> 00:16:26.986
infiltrated the Soul Society
as a Ryoka,

00:16:27.069 --> 00:16:30.489
I had already foreseen this would
happen and had given my advice.

00:16:31.240 --> 00:16:34.743
<i>You</i> are the one who chose
to needlessly disregard my words.

00:16:35.703 --> 00:16:38.497
Everything that is happening now
stems from the fact that

00:16:38.831 --> 00:16:40.708
<i>you</i>, Head Captain,

00:16:40.791 --> 00:16:46.213
couldn't kill that man
1,000 years ago!

00:17:06.608 --> 00:17:08.360
Oh, dear.

00:17:08.736 --> 00:17:11.196
But man, this guy's tough.

00:17:11.739 --> 00:17:13.699
I can't believe
he's still in one piece

00:17:13.741 --> 00:17:15.743
after that beating
he took from Ayon--

00:17:20.205 --> 00:17:21.540
Impressive…

00:17:21.749 --> 00:17:24.835
The report did not indicate
this kind of power…

00:17:25.711 --> 00:17:30.549
I must advise His Majesty
to adjust the strength of our Blut.

00:17:31.383 --> 00:17:33.302
But before I do that…

00:17:33.927 --> 00:17:36.555
Each and every one of you…

00:17:36.805 --> 00:17:39.183
will die here immediately.

00:17:42.227 --> 00:17:43.187
Not again?!

00:17:56.075 --> 00:17:57.076
Actually…

00:17:57.159 --> 00:17:58.077
Wait, Ayon!

00:17:58.368 --> 00:17:59.244
Stop!

00:17:59.536 --> 00:18:02.706
Perhaps I should say,
"you will <i>live</i> here."

00:18:11.632 --> 00:18:13.342
Sklave Rai.

00:18:13.884 --> 00:18:17.513
A Quincy's basic ability
to focus Reishi.

00:18:17.596 --> 00:18:19.264
When taken to its highest limits,

00:18:19.389 --> 00:18:21.600
it becomes the absolute
subordination of Reishi.

00:18:22.267 --> 00:18:25.145
If possible,
I didn't want to use it…

00:18:25.771 --> 00:18:31.110
because my holy wings would be
tarnished by such wicked beings.

00:18:33.529 --> 00:18:35.239
A wise decision.

00:18:35.656 --> 00:18:36.657
However,

00:18:37.282 --> 00:18:39.535
you've neglected to take
the difference in our power

00:18:39.535 --> 00:18:40.953
into consideration.

00:18:50.921 --> 00:18:52.005
Inoue!

00:18:55.551 --> 00:18:56.552
Sado!

00:18:58.262 --> 00:19:03.976
Whenever I see such a struggle,
it reaffirms my beliefs.

00:19:04.601 --> 00:19:09.523
Is the sight of the weak dying
always so unsightly?

00:19:10.023 --> 00:19:11.525
I cannot stand to watch this.

00:19:12.192 --> 00:19:13.777
Die.

00:19:24.204 --> 00:19:24.997
A Bankai…!

00:19:25.330 --> 00:19:27.249
If I destroy the disk on your head…

00:19:27.374 --> 00:19:29.251
you can't use that absolute
subordination of Reishi anymore,

00:19:29.376 --> 00:19:30.377
can you?!

00:19:30.669 --> 00:19:32.713
Figuring that out is one thing.

00:19:32.796 --> 00:19:35.340
But to actually go for it
takes courage…!

00:19:35.507 --> 00:19:37.217
You really are…

00:19:37.259 --> 00:19:39.469
difficult to deal with,
aren't you?!

00:19:42.306 --> 00:19:43.682
Hurry!
Hurry it up!

00:19:44.016 --> 00:19:45.934
Oh, come on,
what are you talking about?!

00:19:46.310 --> 00:19:49.855
You're the one who said,
<i>"We should save Dondochakka"</i>

00:19:49.980 --> 00:19:53.025
<i>"while Ichigo Kurosaki is</i>
<i>distracting the enemy!"</i>

00:19:53.066 --> 00:19:55.360
That was a close one!

00:19:55.527 --> 00:19:58.614
I didn't think we would have to
go through this much trouble!

00:19:59.198 --> 00:20:03.035
Not only are you heavy
but you chose to hide in the sand!

00:20:03.118 --> 00:20:04.536
That hurts!

00:20:14.046 --> 00:20:16.089
Don't enter without my permission.

00:20:16.548 --> 00:20:17.549
This is the second time.

00:20:17.841 --> 00:20:18.842
What's the meaning of this?

00:20:19.384 --> 00:20:21.303
Are the things written here true?

00:20:22.888 --> 00:20:25.557
I guess that means
you know everything…

00:20:26.058 --> 00:20:27.559
About the Wandenreich…

00:20:27.893 --> 00:20:29.686
About the guy
referred to as "His Majesty"…

00:20:30.395 --> 00:20:31.605
And even about Mom…!

00:20:32.564 --> 00:20:35.734
Uryu…
This has nothing to do with you.

00:20:47.246 --> 00:20:48.830
There's no need to be so tense.

00:20:49.498 --> 00:20:50.791
Sixth Seat Kajomaru…

00:20:51.667 --> 00:20:54.711
Squad 11 is standing by
outside the gate.

00:20:55.462 --> 00:20:56.672
There's no need to worry.

00:20:58.924 --> 00:21:00.592
- What was that?!
- There's a blue light!

00:21:01.176 --> 00:21:02.052
What's going on?!

00:21:03.762 --> 00:21:07.891
Conflict is such
an unpleasant affair.

00:21:10.102 --> 00:21:11.603
{\an8}SQUAD SIX BARRACKS

00:21:10.269 --> 00:21:11.603
- What's that?!
-Is it an enemy attack?!

00:21:11.687 --> 00:21:12.437
{\an8}SQUAD EIGHT BARRACKS - ENGAWA

00:21:12.521 --> 00:21:13.188
{\an8}SQUAD NINE BARRACKS -
EDITORIAL DEPARTMENT

00:21:13.272 --> 00:21:14.273
{\an8}SQUAD THREE'S GUARD AREA

00:21:14.398 --> 00:21:17.109
{\an8}SQUAD SIX'S GUARD AREA

00:21:14.690 --> 00:21:16.984
What the hell…is this?

00:21:17.150 --> 00:21:18.735
{\an8}SQUAD THIRTEEN'S GUARD AREA

00:21:19.111 --> 00:21:21.947
Flaming pillars…of Reishi?

00:21:24.324 --> 00:21:26.285
{\an8}SQUAD 1 THIRD SEAT -
GENSHIRO OKIKIBA

00:21:32.332 --> 00:21:33.625
{\an8}SQUAD 3 THIRD SEAT - RIKU TOGAKUSHI

00:21:33.709 --> 00:21:35.252
{\an8}SQUAD 3 FIFTH SEAT - TAKETSUNA GORI

00:21:35.335 --> 00:21:36.628
{\an8}SQUAD 3 SIXTH SEAT - ASUKA KATAKURA

00:21:37.045 --> 00:21:38.714
Reishi Investigation Team!
How much longer?!

00:21:39.589 --> 00:21:40.632
Spiritual Pressure detected!

00:21:40.799 --> 00:21:42.217
A 93 percent match!

00:21:42.718 --> 00:21:43.844
It's a Quincy!

00:21:53.854 --> 00:21:55.230
Lieutenant Kira!

00:21:56.481 --> 00:21:57.816
How dare you launch
a surprise attack!

00:21:58.525 --> 00:22:00.527
Spiral and Rise, Shunjin!

00:22:00.527 --> 00:22:02.696
Blow, Mogaribue!

00:22:03.739 --> 00:22:04.948
Counteract, Katakage!

00:22:12.748 --> 00:22:13.790
Sorry…

00:22:14.916 --> 00:22:17.085
but our orders are to kill you all.

00:22:25.385 --> 00:22:27.012
Tremble in fear, Soul Reapers.

00:22:28.722 --> 00:22:31.475
The Stern Ritters are going to…

00:22:33.560 --> 00:22:35.687
purge all of you.

00:22:44.488 --> 00:22:47.491
{\an8}<i>Everything we had left behind</i>

00:22:47.616 --> 00:22:51.745
{\an8}<i>Our breaths blending as mist</i>

00:22:51.828 --> 00:22:56.333
{\an8}<i>without form or expression</i>

00:22:56.458 --> 00:23:00.629
{\an8}<i>We lie buried as we glare</i>
<i>into the distance</i>

00:23:00.962 --> 00:23:03.590
{\an8}<i>I can't hear anything</i>

00:23:03.757 --> 00:23:06.635
{\an8}<i>I can't seem to cut anything</i>

00:23:06.676 --> 00:23:09.346
{\an8}<i>It feels like I'm sinking</i>

00:23:09.471 --> 00:23:11.306
{\an8}<i>Falling, falling</i>

00:23:11.390 --> 00:23:12.391
{\an8}<i>Touching</i>

00:23:12.516 --> 00:23:15.852
{\an8}<i>Eyes struck wide open</i>

00:23:15.977 --> 00:23:19.231
{\an8}<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:23:19.356 --> 00:23:25.529
{\an8}<i>The furthest reaches are now visible to us</i>

00:23:25.612 --> 00:23:29.491
{\an8}<i>It cannot be undone</i>
<i>and cannot be stopped</i>

00:23:29.616 --> 00:23:32.828
{\an8}<i>This ensuing struggle</i>

00:23:33.078 --> 00:23:37.624
{\an8}<i>Whisk it away beyond</i>
<i>the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:37.624 --> 00:23:39.668
{\an8}<i>Along with our breaths</i>

00:23:40.127 --> 00:23:41.420
{\an8}<i>Take everything</i>

00:23:41.503 --> 00:23:46.174
{\an8}<i>Whisk it away beyond</i>
<i>the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:46.299 --> 00:23:48.218
{\an8}<i>Along with our futures</i>

00:23:48.343 --> 00:23:50.095
{\an8}<i>Along with our world</i>

00:23:51.179 --> 00:23:54.516
{\an8}<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:23:54.599 --> 00:24:00.814
{\an8}<i>The furthest reaches are now</i>
<i>visible to us</i>

00:24:00.939 --> 00:24:02.941
{\an8}<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:24:03.108 --> 00:24:04.609
{\an8}<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:24:04.776 --> 00:24:08.363
{\an8}<i>As we tear each other down</i>

00:24:12.909 --> 00:24:17.456
<i>"A frostbitten world turns to fire,</i>
<i>a shadow of a wing remains."</i>

00:24:18.665 --> 00:24:24.546
<i>"I try and try again,</i>
<i>it slips away, shadow of a wing."</i>

